data.content:
The issue is that `Assert.AreEqual` expects `(expected, actual)`, but your code passes `(actual, expected)`. This causes misleading failure messages (e.g., "Expected: [result] but was: 5" instead of the reverse).

Fix by swapping the arguments:

```csharp
// Before
Assert.AreEqual(result, 5);
Assert.AreEqual(result, 0);

// After
Assert.AreEqual(5, result);
Assert.AreEqual(0, result);
```

